other_tests.findings: Confirmed SAH; Grade II on the World Federation of Neurosurgical Societies scale and Grade 1 on the Fisher scale.
Showed a large complex right proximal MCA aneurysm, a smaller right distal MCA aneurysm, an aneurysm at the basilar tip, and another on the superior cerebellar artery.

Revealed heavy calcification with 50% narrowing of both common carotid arteries; common femoral, external iliac, and internal iliac arteries were patent but exhibited reduced caliber; aortoiliac occlusion was seen.
The treated aneurysms are stable; untreated distal MCA aneurysm remains unchanged in size and configuration.
other_tests.changes_over_time: Stable condition for treated aneurysms; untreated distal MCA aneurysm remains unchanged.
